            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Text B: Monument of Petros … [who died?] in the year 322(?) on the 17th (day) of Peritios
                    (?). Be of good cheer, no one (is) immortal. He died<lb/> Text A: … years old. Be of good
                    cheer, no one (is) immortal.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>This inscription bears two separate texts. The final three lines are the oldest
                    ones. The text extended above the original probably belongs to a later period
                    and has been carved by someone unfamilar with the Greek language who simply
                    copied letters and words unsuccessfully.</p>
            </div>
